commit_message:
Remove cached console auth token after migration

After migrating to another server, the cached instance console auth
tokens become invalid, so we remove the tokens associated with the instance.

Fix bug #1214829

Co-authored-by: Takashi Natsume <natsume.takashi@lab.ntt.co.jp>
Change-Id: I7fddcd13da128a6bec5e2cdb6fa8c8636d6adb24

commit_message:
Port server actions unittests to V3 API Part 1

This changeset just copies the test file to the V3 directory.
Part 2 will make the changes required to test against the
V3 API

Partially implements blueprint v3-api-unittests

Change-Id: I1e73832c567d69d8e428133f5258ac09cfdb74b7

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-19 15:16:41.000000000', 'message': 'proxy: memory storage driver + tests + fixes

Adds a memory storage driver to marconi-proxy. This is ideal for
testing storage implementations.

Furthermore, unit tests are added for the storage layer. These tests
check the fundamental behavior of the proxy storage drivers and
mirrors the approach used by marconi/queues/storage.

The storage interface has also been updated. The old variant keep
round robin indices in storage. I found that this was a Bad Idea. This
patch removes this design flaw from the
implementation. Consequentially, many of the helper functions were
greatly simplified. See: utils/node:weighted_select and
utils/round_robin:Selector.

The last set of changes relate to the transport layer. They are as
follows:
- redis has been torn out of the transport
    * storage is no longer hard-coded
- partition and catalogue controllers are passed as needed to
  resources
- resources round-robin per request, rather than only once on queue
  allocation
- terminology update: nodes -> hosts

Change-Id: I78863f7437dd9eec011cdfe7962fd88be23a3975
'}, {'created': '2013-09-19 15:16:41.000000000', 'message': 'proxy: memory storage driver + tests + fixes

Adds a memory storage driver to marconi-proxy. This is ideal for
testing storage implementations.

Furthermore, unit tests are added for the storage layer. These tests
check the fundamental behavior of the proxy storage drivers and
mirrors the approach used by marconi/queues/storage.

The storage interface has also been updated. The old variant keep
round robin indices in storage. I found that this was a Bad Idea. This
patch removes this design flaw from the
implementation. Consequentially, many of the helper functions were
greatly simplified. See: utils/node:weighted_select and
utils/round_robin:Selector.

The last set of changes relate to the transport layer. They are as
follows:
- redis has been torn out of the transport
    * storage is no longer hard-coded
- partition and catalogue controllers are passed as needed to
  resources
- resources round-robin per request, rather than only once on queue
  allocation

commit_message:
proxy: memory storage driver + tests + fixes

Adds a memory storage driver to marconi-proxy. This is ideal for
testing storage implementations.

Furthermore, unit tests are added for the storage layer. These tests
check the fundamental behavior of the proxy storage drivers and
mirrors the approach used by marconi/queues/storage.

The storage interface has also been updated. The old variant keep
round robin indices in storage. I found that this was a Bad Idea. This
patch removes this design flaw from the
implementation. Consequentially, many of the helper functions were
greatly simplified. See: utils/node:weighted_select and
utils/round_robin:Selector.

The last set of changes relate to the transport layer. They are as
follows:
- redis has been torn out of the transport
    * storage is no longer hard-coded
- partition and catalogue controllers are passed as needed to
  resources
- resources round-robin per request, rather than only once on queue
  allocation
- terminology update: nodes -> hosts

Change-Id: I78863f7437dd9eec011cdfe7962fd88be23a3975
Implements: blueprint placement-service

commit_message:
Fixes unexpected exception message in ProjectUserQuotaNotFound

When an exception ProjectUserQuotaNotFound occurs, the message "Quota
could not be found" was obtained. This is because the name of the
variable to override is incorrect. There is a similar bug in
ConsoleTypeUnavailable and ISERTargetNotFoundForVolume.

Change-Id: If709aff55b9042eaca49aaebddc31c366681a36c
Closes-Bug: #1221527

commit_message:
XenAPI raise InstanceNotFound in _get_vm_opaque_ref

If _get_vm_opaque_ref doesn't find an instance it should raise a
specific InstanceNotFound exception rather than the general NotFound
exception.  Callers of this method may try to catch InstanceNotFound or
NotFound and now both will work.

This fix will prevent a traceback during the _sync_power_states periodic
task which is expecting an InstanceNotFound exception.

Change-Id: Ia28fe33d69520806dab878c843fe435e018a20de

Previously for migration 201 the indexes dictionary was overwritten
causing the assertIn statement to tests against itself. This patch
fixes it so that the test checks the new indexes are created
correctly against the table and also checks they are removed on

Fixes bug 1226924

Change-Id: Ie518041c6b7d534ed1b96e2f9b4e7206f4b68d87

commit_message:
Fix migration 201 tests to actually test changes

Previously for migration 201 the indexes dictionary was overwritten
causing the assertIn statement to tests against itself. This patch
fixes it so that the test checks the new indexes are created
correctly against the table and also checks they are removed on
downgrade.

Fixes bug 1226924

Change-Id: Ie518041c6b7d534ed1b96e2f9b4e7206f4b68d87

commit_message:
Remove ldap identity domain attribute options

LDAP Identity backend is not domain aware, and therefore does not
need mappings for the domain attributes for user and group.

closes-bug: 1209440
Change-Id: Ib7b77b90134322d04b5826b151d05535b9b8b7c7

commit_message:
Allow resource_by_refid returning resumed resources

Resumed resources aren't returned by resource_by_refid, which causes problem
after a stack is resumed.

Fixes bug #1227032

Change-Id: I87893a04bb267e1b42b55f3c60c22a6268ae4464

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-17 13:15:05.000000000', 'message': 'Fixes vol restore discard leaves final bytes unzeroed

When doing a volume restore with Ceph backend to a non-rbd volume
that is greater in size that the backup volume, we write zeroes
the extraneous extents but we are not zeroing the final few bytes
in the case where the destination volume is non-rbd.

Change-Id: Iac1ff98a75e9164f8865c2f7d998454205e049d4
Fixes: bug 1226555
'}, {'created': '2013-09-17 19:43:02.000000000', 'message': 'Fixes vol restore discard leaves final bytes unzeroed

the extraneous extents but we are not zeroing the final few bytes
in the case where the destination volume is non-rbd.

commit_message:
Fixes vol restore discard final bytes unzeroed

When doing a volume restore with Ceph backend to a non-rbd volume
that is greater in size that the backup volume, we write zeroes
the extraneous extents but we are not zeroing the final few bytes
in the case where the destination volume is non-rbd.

Also fixed up internationalisation on a number of log messages.

Change-Id: Iac1ff98a75e9164f8865c2f7d998454205e049d4
Fixes: bug 1226555

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-21 06:19:51.000000000', 'message': 'Remove weakref usage

If a connection escapes the scope of the
backend object, then python will actually
garbage collection the backend object even
though the connection object has a property
that allows you to fetch the backend. If the
property is used after the gc occurs a weakref
failure occurs.

Python is smart enough to correctly deallocate
these types of links by itself so lets just let
it do that.

Change-Id: I49d36b74f896bd1be6c7a1a373b07bdaded3ef4b

commit_message:
Remove weakref usage

If a connection escapes the scope of the
backend object, then python will actually
garbage collect the backend object even
though the connection object has a property
that allows you to fetch the backend. If the
property is used after the gc occurs a weakref
failure occurs.

Python is smart enough to correctly deallocate
these types of object links by itself so lets
just let it do that.

Fixes: bug 1228968

Change-Id: I49d36b74f896bd1be6c7a1a373b07bdaded3ef4b

commit_message:
Allow access to attributes of resumed resources

RESUME COMPLETE|IN_PROGRESS were not treated as valid states while resolving
attribute, thus causing Fn::GetAtt to fail after a stack is resumed.

Fixes bug #1227025

Change-Id: I37b900c61b7d3017afe75fa726597f458be95d93

(1 inline comment)

I had quite a few more comments on this review. Instead, I've decided to call those comments out of scope. This is a good patch for Havana, but I would like to see us more generally support vCenter beyond merely clusters.

I've opened this blueprint to support that work and intend to introduce it in Icehouse:

https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/vmware-auto-inventory

This will require deprecating behavior at line 402 of driver.py (in this patch) which explicitly causes the driver to fail when clusters are not in use. Considering we do not actually have a way to enable non-clustered use of hosts by OpenStack ... this is a better mode than silently failing.

I would want us to remove that line and instead plug-in a "host selector" object that could then interact with the inventory. The simplest selector could just listen to the scheduler, more sophisticated selectors could be smarter as needed by the cloud administrator.'}, {'account_id': 4395, 'date': '2013-08-21 22:10:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

commit_message:
Fixes host stats for VMWareVCDriver

Host stats for VCDriver should collect aggregate cluster stats
rather than that of a single host in the cluster.

Fixes: bug #1190515
Change-Id: I37e46995c5da2e3052e8178098afee7c8061bb3c

commit_message:
Storwize/SVC: Optional CHAP authentication

The Storwize/SVC driver doesn't work with Nova drivers that don't
support CHAP (e.g., HyperV). This patch makes CHAP optional.

DocImpact

Closes-Bug: #1224334
Change-Id: I22df4b916b2800a53c1e4968913f7e95965eaf4b

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-03 19:31:53.000000000', 'message': 'Require assisted_volume_snapshots from novaclient

The "QEMU-assisted-snapshots for GlusterFS volumes" patch currently
does a try/except ImportError for the new assisted_volume_snapshots
extension in novaclient.  Once that functionality is merged into
novaclient, Cinder should consider this a hard requirement rather
than allowing it to be absent.

Related to blueprint qemu-assisted-snapshots

Change-Id: I5d5b4918f17f26706bed361cbbe8b369b10b0b98
'}, {'created': '2013-09-03 19:31:53.000000000', 'message': 'Require assisted_volume_snapshots from novaclient

The "QEMU-assisted-snapshots for GlusterFS volumes" patch currently
does a try/except ImportError for the new assisted_volume_snapshots
extension in novaclient.  Once that functionality is merged into
novaclient, Cinder should consider this a hard requirement rather
than allowing it to be absent.

commit_message:
Require assisted_volume_snapshots from novaclient

The "QEMU-assisted-snapshots for GlusterFS volumes" patch currently
does a try/except ImportError for the new assisted_volume_snapshots
extension in novaclient.  That functionality is now in novaclient
2.15.0, so Cinder should consider this a hard requirement rather
than allowing it to be absent.

Change-Id: I5d5b4918f17f26706bed361cbbe8b369b10b0b98

commit_message:
Document neutron health monitor and pool properties

This adds descriptions to the properties of OS::Neutron::HealthMonitor
and OS::Neutron::Pool, as well as gettext wrapping for the attributes
description

Closes-Bug: #1224172
Change-Id: I1b7a974b8e8b557bd0ed56f3c08c43f385106738

commit_message:
Fix volume_glance_metadata deletion (backport)

Backport patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/41768/ and
its dependency: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/41601/
(no snapshot handling exception, for this is not trivial
due to specific havana changes)

If volume_glance_metadata does not exist for a certain volume,
it returns an exception and does not delete volume from db.
Avoid deleting it if it does not exist.

Fixes bug: 1209367

Change-Id: Icb34c90b13aac1e92b4645c3016127a2d4b8af6f

commit_message:
Fix book building

The args parameter to apply_async really needs to be (book, ), otherwise
nothing is passed and no books are build.

Change-Id: Icae89df5734b1be58f0e6ec8aecc1a31aef365f4

commit_message:
Skip hidden files while traversion rootwrap filters

Hidden files are usually leftovers (like .e.g. .filter.conf~),
don't handle them.

[{'created': '2013-09-23 16:58:35.000000000', 'message': "Fixes to Vagrant testing support.

* Hacked around the fact that chef-zero provisioner doesn't understand .rb files by
running multiple provisioners.

* Fixed call to nova:identity_registration in os-compute-setup.rb role

note: chef run errors with 'No such file or directory - /etc/init.d/quantum-server restart', but can still start a compute instance and access via network, not a showstopper.

Change-Id: I4f9a0d10afb341b43809412e6e79d04b82b15555
"}]
commit_message:
Fixes to Vagrant testing support.

* Hacked around the fact that chef-zero provisioner doesn't understand .rb files by
running multiple provisioners.

* Fixed call to nova:identity_registration in os-compute-setup.rb role

note: chef run errors with 'No such file or directory - /etc/init.d/quantum-server restart', but can still start a compute instance and access via network, not a showstopper.

Change-Id: I4f9a0d10afb341b43809412e6e79d04b82b15555

[{'created': '2013-09-17 14:47:50.000000000', 'message': "Fix for status always in PENDING_CREATE for Edge service router

The root cause is when deployment finished, we only update router status to
active if the status is in pending create. The problem happens when the
background sync thread update router status to active, so the status update
for vcns_router_binding table is skipped. We fixed this by seperating
checking and updating status for router and binding table.

Also fixed an issue where Edge is not deleted if neutron service is
restarted. The root cause is when neutron service restarts, the cache for
router type is empty. And because we delete the router from db before
we delete Edge, we're not able to locate the router from db to determine
the router type. The fix is to use binding table to determine the router
type.

Closes-Bug: #1226229

commit_message:
Fix for status always in PENDING_CREATE for Edge service router

The root cause is when deployment finished, we only update router status to
active if the status is in pending create. The problem happens when the
background sync thread update router status to active, so the status update
for vcns_router_binding table is skipped. We fixed this by seperating
checking and updating status for router and binding table.

Also fixed an issue where Edge is not deleted if neutron service is
restarted. The root cause is when neutron service restarts, the cache for
router type is empty. And because we delete the router from db before
we delete Edge, we're not able to locate the router from db to determine
the router type. The fix is to use binding table to determine the router
type.

Also piggyback a missing attribute for updating Edge interface. It must have
been removed by accident when resolving conflict during service plugin merge.

Closes-Bug: #1226229
Change-Id: I3d0639d245e71ea2a3faba70fef1a0ebb87e19fd

commit_message:
Collection named based on resource type

To be more consistent with other existing OpenStack APIs, the collection
name is now based on the requested resource type. Also, the link to the
next subset of the collection is now an attribute on the root document
of the request body.

Change-Id: Ie0f99d975b691aad7cd39fddd7d141f95c7912f8
Closes-Bug: #1227928

commit_message:
Fix over-indent in compute/nova

There are two lines in compute/nova.py that uses 8 spaces indent,
this simple patch correct those to 4 spaces.

Change-Id: I8f7849385ef59a085b5e3cc45954a2f2a19442ee

commit_message:
VMware: ensure that resource exists prior to accessing

Ensure that the resource being accessed actually exists. There
may be cases when a cluster is updated/deleted and the scheduler
may be out of sync with the compute node.

Fixes bug: 1216510

Change-Id: Ib82af10f78fbad0cec55eff3dffd3d36409d8b24

commit_message:
cleaned up some roles to make it possible to install allinone openstack server using role[allinone-compute]

* removed unnecessary roles
* provided Vagrantfile and supporting files to allow for allinone openstack install in vagrant

Change-Id: I59a0a89e8ecd4cf683c344c1f7a4abea3d0cf38a

commit_message:
xenapi: Use C locale

By exporting the LC_ALL=C we can get rid of localisation issues, as the
actual scripts are already assuming an english installation.

FIxes bug 1227527

Change-Id: Ieeebce4d53b09959146a970f3fb803201ac5ebdf

Just a suggestion: this might be more cleanly done by creating a custom column type in the sqlalchemy model that uses a Decimal column for storage on mysql and a DateTime on other dialects.  

This way the column type becomes an implementation detail of the model, all the conversion is done by the custom type, and is not seen by the code outside of that. Also, this way you can use the numeric type for MySQL, but leave the other db's which have decent datetime implementations alone. 

Here's some info on that:
http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_0_8/core/types.html#sqlalchemy.types.TypeDecorator"}, {'account_id': 7368, 'date': '2013-09-16 18:31:45.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
Fix for timestamp precision in SQLAlchemy

This fix adds the PreciseTimestamp custom type to address how
MySQL < 5.6.4 truncates temporal columns to the second:
http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.6/en/fractional-seconds.html

Change-Id: I9d324d1cb6867cf99e15e2ecdc566dc5f8fef536
Closes-Bug: #1215676

commit_message:
Remove change_apache_user_group function

This function allowed you to change the process running user for all of
apache. This is better handled on a per-process basis.

Change-Id: I165adc0c49fc328f34835856b49983c4e189f143
Fixes: bug 1226346
Fixes: bug 1225853

vagrant-chef-zero and vagrant-omnibus. Unfortunately Chef Zero does not

commit_message:
Initial Vagrant testing support, using the Chef provider with Chef Zero.

The Vagrant box is the default 12.04 and 13.04 provided by Opscode's Bento
project. It uses the Vagrant plugins vagrant-berkshelf, vagrant-cachier,
vagrant-chef-zero and vagrant-omnibus. Unfortunately Chef Zero does not
understand .rb files yet, so we're using the recipes directly in the run
list. This also means that searching by roles is broken so this needs to be
fixed ASAP.

Change-Id: I5fe8b175f15c4a21c16de46bc05ec6a0c27cfdaa

commit_message:
Nested stack derive requires_deferred_auth from resources

StackResource requires_deferred_auth needs to determine
its value from the requires_deferred_auth of the nested
stack.

Change-Id: I206390b3f2fe099d88f255bdff81d2abe2496333
Closes-Bug: #1223054

commit_message:
GlusterFS: Copy snap from correct source file

The GlusterFS driver's copy_volume_from_snapshot was previously
not parsing the snapshot information to determine which backing
file to copy from, instead copying from the active file at all
times.  This would result in the wrong data being supplied when
a volume is cloned from a snapshot.

Add a test for the copy_volume_from_snapshot method.

Closes-Bug: #1222907
Change-Id: Ib829ca1a6812b61845f3b2eb9c5507779fa6ec15

commit_message:
GlusterFS: Use image_utils for qemu-img calls

Code added for GlusterFS snapshot support in Havana included
new code to parse qemu-img output.  This removes this code
and uses image_utils qemu_img_info instead.

Add test to image_utils for parsing a different style of
qemu-img info output.

Improve GlusterFS driver test coverage with tests for cloning,
create from snapshot, and initialize_connection.

Closes-Bug: #1224030
Change-Id: I8f1811b400c06edb3cd7416c52aa297921841e54

commit_message:
Port Cisco nexus and network db UT to ML2 mech driver UT

Fixes bug 1227964

This fix ports the Cisco Nexus database and network database
unit tests to the Cisco ML2 mechanism driver UT.
The existing test scripts which are ported:
    neutron/tests/unit/cisco/test_nexus_db.py
    neutron/tests/unit/cisco/test_network_db.py
The new test scripts are:
    neutron/tests/unit/ml2/drivers/test_cisco_nexus_db.py
    neutron/tests/unit/ml2/drivers/test_cisco_network_db.py

Note that the QoS database related tests in
test_network_db.py are not ported because QoS is
not currently supported in the Cisco ML2
mechanism driver.

Change-Id: Ib47dab9dafde7c4b8cf0a4930379750f00b9455c

commit_message:
Raises error if duplicate keys found in DictOpt

DictOpt didn't report when the input values had duplicate keys.
This would be a problem if the user had put in duplicate keys in
the conf file and the service didn't work as expected.
(c.f) Neutrons provider network mapping options
This patch raises a ConfigFileValueError when duplicate keys are found.

Fixes bug #1228995

Change-Id: I91e1bd0eda4ed4fd6c7eb6ea5d4a89d583d1305e

Fix create's response is different with requested for sec-grps V3

The create's response always shows the default security-groups even the request
with different security-groups.

Fix bug 1221651

Change-Id: I0c3de3c4d00ed15f3e4a0717c0a1f123ccbf3068

commit_message:
VMware: bug fix for instance deletion with attached volume

The creation of the connection information required by Cinder to
delete the volume accessed a resource that did not exist (as it had
been deleted). This would result in the instance being in a 'DELETING'
state and the Cinder volume in 'in-use' state.

Fixes bug 1223074

Change-Id: I5283b1ddea76c0eaaf7315fc8cf8969c6cd6755f

commit_message:
Funtional Tests should call glance.db.get_api

The test_registry , test_simple and test_sqlalchemy tests import the
modules directly instead of calling get_api of db/__init__.py
With the introduction of db_pool, they should use the get_api method.

Also adds a tear down to the ThreadPoolWrapper tests to fix jenkins
issues related to the CONF using tpool set to True in the tests.

Fixes Bug #1223167
Change-Id: I66e9f5fba449107ad92e895f6a9e550e0bcddf1c

commit_message:
Fixes test scripts with wrong bitmode

Some modules have bitmode 755. Changed to 644

Added a redundant blank line according to hacking's import template.
https://github.com/openstack-dev/hacking/blob/master/HACKING.rst

This was done to avoid merged errors in gerrit which happens
if no content has changed.

Partially fixes bug #1224226

Floating IP assignement support

Node Group Templates now have field with floating ip Pools.

'}, {'account_id': 7133, 'date': '2013-09-17 14:59:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

'}, {'account_id': 642, 'date': '2013-09-17 16:01:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I'm personally torn on this:I can see how this would fix it, but in the bug report itself you mention that a bug exists for fixing the broken terminated_at cases. Seems like identifying what those are and adding some finally: blocks would solve this, no? This fix essentially hides the problem, since we're just removing code that depends on that field being set."}, {'account_id': 236, 'date': '2013-09-17 16:28:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I'm a bit worried about the semantics of this change. Generally, 'terminated_at' is when we delete the instance, and 'deleted_at' is when we delete the db record. 

If they mean effectively the same thing (i.e. if we always delete the record immediately after terminating the instance) then perhaps we should get rid of the terminated_at column altogether, as it is redundant. 

If they are *not* effectively the same, then this changes the semantics of the audit, which is worrysome, since this info is often used for billing purposes. 

In either case, there are several other uses of terminated_at which should be consistant with this, including the deleted_at date in notifications (which is currently actually terminated_at. This was changed at some point (for reasons I don't recall atm) which is somewhat of a red flag. )"}, {'account_id': 236, 'date': '2013-09-17 16:32:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

also, if this is changed to use deleted_at, right now there is an index added on terminated_at and launched_at specifically to speed up this query. If it is changed, we should change the index.'}, {'account_id': 5652, 'date': '2013-09-17 16:38:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Phil's bug report says that deleted_at is more correct for this case than terminated_at.  I'd be happy to hear more opinions.

In any case, if this gets rejected then I think we still want the new unit test.  (But not until Icehouse since it would no longer be a bugfix.)"}, {'account_id': 1501, 'date': '2013-09-18 11:18:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I think the schematics of the audit code is currently wrong.

terminated_at and deleted_at are in practice pretty much the same thing, and only an failure in the deletion or a bug can lead to one being set without the other.   

However accepting that small gap between these two events in normal processing, the current code will stop generating "exists" messages once the instance has been terminated even if it still exists in the system.   

The proposed change would stop generating exists messages once the instance has been deleted, even if the termination fails somehow (Other code in the system will already reap or report the VM in this case).'}, {'account_id': 1501, 'date': '2013-09-18 11:23:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Matt - for sure the original bug should be (has been) fixed, and anyone exposed to it needs to clean up their DB (its a pity IMO that bug fixes don't include this in their scope as well, but that's another issue)

The reason I raised the bug was not to get a workaround to that issue, but because I think the logic for "exists" should be based around existence (i.e not deleted) rather that some other state (i.e not terminated).   

There are still some error conditions where an instance could be terminated and not deleted, and in such cases the instance is still the responsibility of the host and could be consuming resources there - hence not generating exists messages for it seems wrong.'}, {'account_id': 1501, 'date': '2013-09-18 11:49:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

See also:  https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1227080

If this remapping of names / concepts wasn't in the notification code then the receiving system would at least have had a chance of understanding the true state of the instance."}, {'account_id': 1501, 'date': '2013-09-19 15:27:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

'}, {'account_id': 5387, 'date': '2013-09-20 18:15:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Phil, in regards to having terminated_at set but deleted not being set. I was investigating an issue yesterday where instances where getting into this state. It does appear that the instances themselves were deleted from the hypervisor, and compute errored afterwards.

As others said, I think this is addressing the symptoms, and not the actual cause...."}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2013-09-23 13:56:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I'm on the side of thinking that the existing use of terminated_at makes the most sense here"}, {'account_id': 5652, 'date': '2013-09-23 14:57:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Abandoned

I think that's enough votes against to withdraw this and let reviewers focus on other issues."}]

commit_message:
Make instance_get_active_by_window_joined check deleted_at

Previously, it used terminated_at, which is set less consistently.

Also add a unit test for instance_get_active_by_window_joined, which
was previously missing one, to verify that the change worked.

Fixes bug 1226036

Change-Id: If5e69b4e79d67b7d7076f73507aa0bdaa93c01d1

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-12 07:21:34.000000000', 'message': 'Cleanup of tenantId, tenant_id, and default_project_id

This patchset normalizes the use of tenantId, tenant_id, and
default_project_id across the Identity backend.  This includes
making default_project_id no longer part of the "extra" json blob
on the user object and migrating all "tenantId" "tenant_id" and
"default_project_id" into the new column (SQL).

In the LDAP driver, businessCategory is now the mapping for
default_project_id by default as domain_id is stripped off for
drivers (ldap) that are not domain_aware.  "default_project_id"
is still (by default) configured to be in the "ignore" attributes
for the LDAP driver, so 'tenantId' and 'default_project_id' will
not be returned on the user object (or in user_ref) unless the
Keystone is explicitly configured to do so.

closes-bug: 1209440
closes-bug: 1219739
Change-Id: I07f9dfe111646884ac5efd42fc8c2974188b3b94

making default_project_id no longer part of the "extra" json blob
on the user object and migrating all "tenantId" "tenant_id" and
"default_project_id" into the new column (SQL).

In the LDAP driver, businessCategory is now the mapping for
default_project_id by default as domain_id is stripped off for
drivers (ldap) that are not domain_aware.  "default_project_id"
is still (by default) configured to be in the "ignore" attributes
for the LDAP driver, so 'tenantId' and 'default_project_id' will
not be returned on the user object (or in user_ref) unless
Keystone is explicitly configured to do so.

closes-bug: 1209440
closes-bug: 1219739
Change-Id: I07f9dfe111646884ac5efd42fc8c2974188b3b94

commit_message:
Cleanup of tenantId, tenant_id, and default_project_id

This patchset normalizes the use of tenantId, tenant_id, and
default_project_id across the Identity backend.  This includes
making default_project_id no longer part of the "extra" json blob
on the user object and migrating all "tenantId" "tenant_id" and
"default_project_id" into the new column (SQL).

In the LDAP driver, None is set as the mapping for
default_project_id.  This means that use of default_project_id with
LDAP Identity will require an explicit mapping to be defined by the
cloud operator.

"default_project_id" remains (by default) configured to be in the
"ignore" attributes for the LDAP driver, so 'tenantId' and
'default_project_id' will not be saved on the user_object during
update or create unless Keystone is explicitly configured to do so.

closes-bug: 1219739
closes-bug: 1226475
related-bug: 1201251
Change-Id: I07f9dfe111646884ac5efd42fc8c2974188b3b94

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-14 16:44:50.000000000', 'message': 'Mark Memcache and System Time section as obsolete with Havana

Code has been introduced so that the Memcache token does not depend
on UTC as system time anymore, so this section is obsolete with
Havana.

commit_message:
Remove obsolete Memcache and System Time section

Code has been introduced so that the Memcache token does not depend
on UTC as system time anymore, so this section is obsolete with
Havana.

Change-Id: I07b097309c9740cb6462fafc286fcb8712251010
Closes-Bug: #1221087

commit_message:
Ensure names are truncated to accommodate NVP limit

Switches created through Advanced Plugin should have
their name truncated as well. To this aim, move things
around to avoid awkward imports or code duplications

Fixes bug #1227927

Change-Id: I3cc69356227d3bd63603ee1e53d82e6561f4cad0

commit_message:
Syncs install_venv_common.py from oslo-incubator

Needed to make run_tests.sh identify requirements correctly

We need to check requirements.txt and test-requirements.txt
in parallel to ensure both are satisfied and we don't upgrade
a package beyond requirements.txt's limits when installing
dependencies for test-requirements.txt

Fixes bug: 1227019

Change-Id: I606f8a1d3eed5c270d5b3c154994d5c3a17b98c8

commit_message:
Fix default config file generation and add a check

This fixes the default configuration sample generator by registering
securemessage option globally. To avoid such regression in the future,
adding a run of the script in the pep8 target should be a good start.

Change-Id: I81ea3366cc8eb0be33fdcf3092e9c9b91757e165

commit_message:
Improve validation tools

To use test.py in gating jobs, two options have been added that
set default values. That way, we can have in the Jenkins files
only the master switch and can control ourselves if we want to
change what exactly is run as part of such a gate job.

For validation we do not recurse the whole tree anymore
if we only validate single files.

A verbose mode has been added.
Each pass shows now the number of files processed and only outputs
filenames if --verbose is given.
Additionally, formatting has been cleaned up by using pylint and pep8.
pep8 reports no warnings or errors now.

Example outputs of test.py:
$ tools/test.py --job-niceness

Validating files...
  config-reference/ch_networkingconfigure.xml: trailing or unnecessary
whitespaces found in lines: 13
...
Validation failed, validated 14 files.

$ tools/test.py --job-build

Checking that no removed files are referenced...
Passed removed file check, 41 files were removed, 627 files checked.

Validating files...
Validation passed, validated 14 files.

Queuing the following books for building:
  config-reference
  install-guide
  admin-guide-network
Building all books now...
>>> Build of book admin-guide-network succeeded.
>>> Build of book install-guide succeeded.
>>> Build of book config-reference succeeded.

Change-Id: Ia443553b6c774df7e72ef7c0d8768badfb34bc6d

commit_message:
Move install and config info from Network Admin Guide to Install Guide and Config Ref

Applied systemitem and programlisting tags where indicated by reviewers
Deleted extra spaces after =s and also other white spaces
Fixed a couple of typos - major copyedit to be done under another bug

Closes-bug: 1223542
Change-Id: Ia4ecbdb304e18a42769b50d52d33e3757710fe5b
Author: Nermina Miller

commit_message:
Use the new alarm format

The change sync the client API with the new alarm type and keep
compatibility with the previous format of the alarm.

It allows to create the new type of alarm: combination alarm.

Implements blueprint alarming-logical-combination

Change-Id: Ie62265023cadc20cf36a0d0b3775f4d984e324cf

commit_message:
Move comment in service.py to correct location

As part of change I21a45862 in nova review feedback was provided
that service.py has a comment in the wrong location.  The comment
needs to be moved, but to address this properly, we need to
move the comment in oslo-incubator.  This way the service.py
code will match up between the two projects.

Fixes bug: 1227375

Change-Id: I1f99bc98f7b8396fd82f139dee2419765e5eab3b

commit_message:
[VMware] Fix problem transferring files with ipv6 host

Need to protect the host name with '[' and ']' before
we create a http/https connection

Fixes LP# 1224479

Change-Id: I8c2e58d3eb5e001eff3c9354c3cdc593469b23ac

'}, {'account_id': 4491, 'date': '2013-09-03 08:06:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(4 inline comments)

Another question: Is it possible that when one master is distributing the alarms slowly, a newly started partition becomes the master and distributing the alarms very quickly, finished the distribution before the old master. Will the later arrived distribution rpc messages from the old master result in the situation that the same alarm is being evaluated by 2 partitions? Is it OK?"}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2013-09-03 09:26:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Well the newly started partition shouldn't become the master as its start timestamp will be newer than that of the existing master. Unless you're thinking of a clock-skew type of scenario?

But even in that case, the old master will see the presence reports from the new master, realize that an apparently older potential master is available and step back from the mastership role.

Then once the new master has determined that it should assume the master role, it will do a re-balance and re-allocate all the alarms.

Now there is an assumption that the re-balances from the old and new masters don't overlap, i.e. it's not possible that a allocation from an older re-balance is received by a partition after an allocation from a newer re-balance. Though I guess we could abort a long-running allocation if a newer master is detected during the re-balance. Would that address your concern?

Cheers,
Eoghan"}, {'account_id': 4491, 'date': '2013-09-03 10:41:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: No score

@eglynn, how about the following corner case:

When an old master is executing the long time operation api_client.alarms.list() in the method _assume_mastership(), a new partition is come online. When the new partition is determining the master(_is_master()), it hasn't received the presence message from the old master so it decides to be the new master. Then the old master's presence message arrives at the new master just before the new master begins to _distribute(). In this case, the old master might executing assign() first and then the _distribute() from the original _assume_mastership(). So the self.assignment of the old master might contains duplicated alarms as the new master."}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2013-09-03 10:44:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Could that be addressed with a longer warm-up period?

i.e. avoid grabbing mastership until say at least 2*eval_interval has elapsed from the partitions start-time?

Cheers,
Eoghan'}, {'account_id': 4491, 'date': '2013-09-03 10:59:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

yes, I think that might help.'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2013-09-03 11:28:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(5 inline comments)

That looks pretty good to me. I see this as a direct implementation of the mechanism you imagined, so it is still a bit confusing to read (at least to me). I think it could be enlightened a bit by using more abstraction in some place and a better description of the workflow, but that could be done in a second pass. Waiting for the test suite :)"}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-09-14 06:03:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Forgot to say: I'm a bit worried some part of the code are tied to the threshold evaluator, I think it should be generic to be able to use the alarm combination evaluator too."}, {'account_id': 688, 'date': '2013-09-19 14:24:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

Assuming N alarms and M evaluation services, this approach allocates N/M alarms per service. This can be done easier by having a queue topic per partition. The partition can be determined by alarm.uuid mod M. It self-balances and we can easily support multiple evaluators per partition. 

No fan out. No timers/pings. 

You should verify also that fanout will still be available in oslo.messaging. 

That said, the alarm evaluator proposal I have in my alarm improvement doc wouldn't require any partitioning at all. Something to consider."}, {'account_id': 688, 'date': '2013-09-19 14:37:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

Also, how will this perform when we're rebalancing every time an alarm is added/deleted?

And I'm wondering about an alarm that's on the fence-post of a partition and ensuring that it gets handled in a timely fashion (or will it only be at the frequency of the rebalancing vs. the evaluator)?"}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2013-09-19 18:34:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: (9 inline comments)

@jd__: thanks for review, responses inline.

WRT to your concern about the assumption of threshold-oriented evaluation, I think that's really just restricted to variable naming etc. ... i.e. it should work equally well with combination evaluation (once that lands) modulo some reconciliation with Medhi's changes to the Evaluator contract.

Cheers,
Eoghan"}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2013-09-19 18:34:14.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 10.'}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2013-09-19 18:35:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

@sandywalsh: thanks for the review!

I've confirmed with the oslo PTL that fanout support will remain in olso.messaging (as discussed just now on IRC).

I'll look into changing over to a topic per partition for the assignment/allocation.

We don't rebalance on every alarm addition or deletion. Added alarms are allocated in an incremental fashion. Deletion only triggers a re-balance when a certain threshold of deletions has occurred since the last re-balance (otherwise the evaluators are tolerant of a deleted alarm remaining in their assignment).

There is no allowance for fencing as yet."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-09-19 19:06:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Works for me

[{'created': '2013-09-02 17:40:48.000000000', 'message': "Simple alarm partitioning protocol based on AMQP fanout RPC

[The tests for this are still WIP so I've excluded them for
now, but given the lateness in the dev cycle, I wanted to
get some eyes on this today.]

All available partitions report their presence periodically.

The priority of each partition in terms of assuming mastership
is determined by earliest start-time (with a UUID-based tiebreaker
in the unlikely event of a time clash).

A single partion assumes mastership at any given time, taking
responsibility for allocating the alarms to be evaluated across
the set of currently available partitions.

When a partition lifecycle event is detected (i.e. a pre-existing
partition fails to report it's presence, or a new one is started
up), a complete rebalance of the alarms is initiated.

Individual alarm lifecycle events, on the other hand, do not
require a full re-balance. Instead new alarms are allocated as
they are detected, whereas deleted alarms are initially alloed to
remain within the allocation (as the individual threshold evaluators
are tolerant of assigned alarms not existing, and the deleted alarms
should essentially be randomly distributed over the partions). However
once the number of alarms deleted since the last rebalance reaches a
certain limit, a rebalance will be initiated to maintain freshness.

Implements bp alarm-service-partitioner

Change-Id: I3dede464d019a7f776f3d302e2b24cc4a9fc5b66
"}, {'created': '2013-09-17 12:52:06.000000000', 'message': "Simple alarm partitioning protocol based on AMQP fanout RPC

All available partitions report their presence periodically.

The priority of each partition in terms of assuming mastership
is determined by earliest start-time (with a UUID-based tiebreaker
in the unlikely event of a time clash).

A single partion assumes mastership at any given time, taking
responsibility for allocating the alarms to be evaluated across
the set of currently available partitions.

When a partition lifecycle event is detected (i.e. a pre-existing
partition fails to report it's presence, or a new one is started
up), a complete rebalance of the alarms is initiated.

Individual alarm lifecycle events, on the other hand, do not
require a full re-balance. Instead new alarms are allocated as
they are detected, whereas deleted alarms are initially alloed to
remain within the allocation (as the individual threshold evaluators
are tolerant of assigned alarms not existing, and the deleted alarms
should essentially be randomly distributed over the partitions).
However once the number of alarms deleted since the last rebalance
reaches a certain limit, a rebalance will be initiated to maintain
freshness.

As presence reports are received, each partition keeps track of the
oldest partition it currently knows about, allowing an assumption of
mastership to be aborted if an older partition belatedly reports.

Implements bp alarm-service-partitioner

Change-Id: I3dede464d019a7f776f3d302e2b24cc4a9fc5b66

in the unlikely event of a time clash).

A single partion assumes mastership at any given time, taking
responsibility for allocating the alarms to be evaluated across
the set of currently available partitions.

When a partition lifecycle event is detected (i.e. a pre-existing
partition fails to report it's presence, or a new one is started
up), a complete rebalance of the alarms is initiated.

Individual alarm lifecycle events, on the other hand, do not
require a full re-balance. Instead new alarms are allocated as
they are detected, whereas deleted alarms are initially allowed to
remain within the allocation (as the individual threshold evaluators
are tolerant of assigned alarms not existing, and the deleted alarms
should essentially be randomly distributed over the partitions).
However once the number of alarms deleted since the last rebalance
reaches a certain limit, a rebalance will be initiated to maintain
freshness.

As presence reports are received, each partition keeps track of the
oldest partition it currently knows about, allowing an assumption of
mastership to be aborted if an older partition belatedly reports.

Implements bp alarm-service-partitioner

commit_message:
Simple alarm partitioning protocol based on AMQP fanout RPC

All available partitions report their presence periodically.

The priority of each partition in terms of assuming mastership
is determined by earliest start-time (with a UUID-based tiebreaker
in the unlikely event of a time clash).

A single partion assumes mastership at any given time, taking
responsibility for allocating the alarms to be evaluated across
the set of currently available partitions.

When a partition lifecycle event is detected (i.e. a pre-existing
partition fails to report its presence, or a new one is started
up), a complete rebalance of the alarms is initiated.

Individual alarm lifecycle events, on the other hand, do not
require a full re-balance. Instead new alarms are allocated as
they are detected, whereas deleted alarms are initially allowed to
remain within the allocation (as the individual evaluators are tolerant
of assigned alarms not existing, and the deleted alarms should be
randomly distributed over the partions). However once the number of
alarms deleted since the last rebalance reaches a certain limit, a
rebalance will be initiated to maintain equity.

As presence reports are received, each partition keeps track of the
oldest partition it currently knows about, allowing an assumption of
mastership to be aborted if an older partition belatedly reports.

The alarm evaluation service to launch (singleton versus partitioned)
is controlled via a new alarm.evaluation_service config option.

Implements bp alarm-service-partitioner

Change-Id: I3dede464d019a7f776f3d302e2b24cc4a9fc5b66

commit_message:
powervm: Add missing kwargs for exception

Exception inherit from NovaException has property 'fmt_msg'. If the
fmt_msg include %(some_key)s , and kwargs is empty when construct
an exception instance, that will raise KeyError.

Closes bug #1229071

Change-Id: I3a9cb7759bde5f4d4d4b35e403beeea10ded9396

commit_message:
Update help string to match API doc

This changes the text to match what we are stating in
the API documentation (clarifying with review 46569).

Since there is no validation, no changes were made for
peer-address, which is now a string and not IPAddress.
Also, we are leaving peer-id as mandatory, per the API
document.

bug-1225129

Change-Id: I9c3f14213785084349b56a4081e34c209b878ec4

commit_message:
Sync requirements with global requirements

* bump alembic to >=0.6.0
* bump python-novaclient to >=2.15.0
* remove version pin for six
* bump pyflakes to >=0.7.2,<0.7.4

commit_message:
Remove version pbr pins from setup_requires

* setuptools can never upgrade things based on setup_requires versions
* actual pbr version range should be defined in requirements.txt

Change-Id: I2deb735b48c29286c4ca4e01e9720bf97a58d348

commit_message:
Move ServiceStatuses from trove.instance to trove.common

This is a part of refactoring intended to reduce dependency
of trove.guestagent on server-side related packages

Implements: blueprint separate-guestagent-related-code

Change-Id: I120d5fcd51bbbaa71b67f841cec37ea7b4358465

commit_message:
Update redstack scripts to install trove using devstack

Cleanup the trove integration scripts so that we can install trove
directly from devstack instead of using local.sh.

Change-Id: I3c6b8a59b4935cd46d38639ad369fe21f35f082e
Fixes: bug 1226315

commit_message:
Fixes inconsistent console problem

The `open console` link in `Network Topology` page is inconsistent with
console in `Instance Detail` page.

Fixes bug 1228990

commit_message:
Use built-in print() instead of print statement

In python 3 print statement is not supported, so we should use
only print() functions.

This patch also removes print in unit test, left by accident

Fixes bug 1226943

Change-Id: I5ace50cb9e149682344b4c986ef9318f8dc50f72

commit_message:
Migrate sqlalchemy utils from Oslo

These utils are useful for work with database and schema migrations.

File `glance/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/migration.py`
- makes it possible to use the unified code for drop unique constrains
  for SQLite backend
- fixes a bug in sqlalchemy-migrate that leads to deletion of existing
  unique constraints of a table when a new one is added (SQLite backend)

File `glance/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/utils.py`
- contains utilites that can be used in database migrations.

File `glance/openstack/common/exception.py`
- contains required exceptions

blueprint db-use-oslo-common-code

Change-Id: I374d35a6fc13231b5eac8b1f90a2f52bfc415a7c

commit_message:
Add a retry to create_iscsi_target for LVM

There's a bug in the tgt driver where under certain
conditions where a race condition is present that can
result in tgtadm attempting re-use a target ID.

Testing this it seems that a retry will address this nicely
and cause tgtd to grab a new target ID and things are ok.

This patch adds a simple check/retry mechanism around the
iscsi_target_create in the LVM driver to catch this issue and
deal with it.

There are a number of bugs that it appears can be attributed to
this, but this patch is associated with the most predominant
clear cut version.

Closes-Bug #1223469

Change-Id: I5126009f196adcafad55e73ff99a59262dd93dfe

commit_message:
Fix issues with failed lvremove

There are some race conditions that
can cause problems with lvremove commands.  In
most cases these seem to recover nicely just
with a simple retry of the lvremove.  Adding
a udev settle seems to elimate the rest of them.

This is a difficult issue to reproduce, and there's
a suspiscion that it relates to failed target
creeates.

The patch adds a catch on the lvremove failure,
followed by a udevadm settle and a retry of the
lvremove.  With the setup that I've been able
to reproduce this issue these changes have eliminated
any force delete failures.

The other option that had been proposed was using dmsetup remove
but there are concerns that this may cause problems.

Change-Id: I2a2b0d0f4fefd0daf9424ab96aaf87ba53ebc171
Closes-Bug: #1191960

commit_message:
Handle long integer conversion in NEC portinfo validation tests

There are a couple of tests for NEC portinfo validation that pass an id
which gets converted to a base-16 integer and then that gets converted
to a hex string. The problem is the integer conversion can make it a
long integer and then the hex built-in appends 'L' to the string, and
the tests do not account for that. This patch handles that case.

Closes-Bug: #1228212

Change-Id: Id3aed686329dae9cc4777213a4d2bcf406652e15

commit_message:
NetApp check for 7 mode controller version

Queries the filer api version and raises error
if the version is unsupported.

Closes-Bug:#1223474

Change-Id: I430a41d63a2541891fdbdb20dacab9f69fa44291

commit_message:
Fix network info injection in pure IPv6 environment

get_non_legacy_network_template assumes that IPv4 is always available

So if i try to use Nova Network without any ipv4 using say
"nova network-create public --fixed-range-v6 fd8c:215d:178e:452:0:0:0:0/64"
then the deployment fails. So fix the code to ensure ipv4 is optional

Fixes LP# 1216178

Change-Id: Ib0c47a49debd4fed83d382a301687df23ca2ec0d

commit_message:
Changes Test, port is not gauranteed unused

When creating new network, first port is no
longer ignored for dhcp use. Setting
device_owner or device_id reserves
port for referenced device.
Fixes: bug #1219795

Depends On Change Id: I6d3c991046221e50c9fe4d9a11c92f5a553c7ba4
Change-Id: Ib2a934e8d9f792e9a7aff7d3554e5d3d1ba0b962

commit_message:
Chart css small fixes

-fix chart tooltip css
-remove redundant display of date (one in the tooltip,
    one at the top of the chart)
-change the legend css (better visual integration)
    - invert background and foreground color
    - remove underline on left tick
    - change tick color to black

Fixes bug #1228031
Change-Id: I45431866cd905209c4dc19f1334beb7cfff54630

commit_message:
Code change for nova support glance ipv6 address

This code change is for nova can parse glance api servers which is
IPv6 address correctly, also make sure nova commands can be run
successfully in pure ipv6 environment, such as 'nova image-list'
and 'nova boot' command.

Fixes bug 1182830

Change-Id: Ia71002c7038b820db7a63f7d6892e76de4743d8d

volume migration. The admin metadata wasn't deleted when the database
row was deleted, resulting in a foreign key violation. Unfortunately
mysql in the gate or devstack configurations doesn't seem to check for
this.

commit_message:
Soft delete tmp migration volume

Previously the row for the temporary migration volume was deleted from
the database, which caused a foreign key violation for its admin
metadata. Regardless, the volume should have been soft deleted from the
database anyway, and this patch takes care of that.

Change-Id: I8e4942b0e21ec79c90aa95b18b5612b5b133fd62
Closes-Bug: #1219097

commit_message:
Revert "Importing correlation_id middleware from oslo-incubator"

This reverts commit 26ecf7b02377b860b4412aa554ed2392f42f8d40.

This patch was merged in preparation for

commit_message:
Improve "keypair data is invalid" error message

When doing a keypair-add, I was hitting a permission denied issue with
ssh-keygen -l. This turned out to be a configuration issue, but the
error message on the client side was pretty unhelpful with debugging
the issue:

  BadRequest: Keypair data is invalid (HTTP 400)

Fix that so we get:

  BadRequest: Keypair data is invalid: failed to generate fingerprint (HTTP 400)

Also fix the other uses of InvalidKeypair so we include the general
"keypair data is invalid" prefix.

Change-Id: I209e76adaf7c18a9f2f2dbb6da62db6c1cd9461e

[{'created': '2013-09-02 07:26:15.000000000', 'message': 'Fixes race cond between delete and confirm resize

If we delete an instance after a confirming resize operation,
and if the instance is deleted firstly at the dest compute node,
then the *_resize dir and network info of this instance will be
left alone on the source compute node, never be cleaned up.
Please refer the bug page to get the reproduce steps

Fixes bug 1202484

commit_message:
Fixes race cond between delete and confirm resize

If we delete an instance after a confirming resize operation,
and if the instance is deleted firstly at the dest compute node,
then the *_resize dir and network info of this instance will be
left alone on the source compute node, never be cleaned up.
Please refer the bug page to get the reproduce steps

Fixes bug 1202484

Change-Id: Ib1e3d976373bd7f4d086d4f9716b0bca4b383bab

commit_message:
Remove two unused config options in baremetal

baremetal.injected_password and injected_network_template are not used
anywhere, so just remove them.

The actual injection config options used, such as net_config_template,
are in baremetal.pxe.

Change-Id: I93b4d2c2303a1ce954c45fc7e9842b18615bd56f

commit_message:
Document Neutron Firewall as a Service

This adds documentation for the Firewall as a Service (FWaaS)
feature being introduced in the Neutron Havana release.

Change-Id: I6cbd62ea295b21e28fa0b95c82d0ef1b46f47c93
Implements: blueprint neutron-fwaas-deployment

commit_message:
VMware: handle exceptions from RetrievePropertiesEx correctly

The commit below did not update the exception handling correctly:

  e331287cdd1300878bfb9bbb3630889370e5fa72

The fault checker should be retrievepropertiesex_fault_checker instead of
retrieveproperties_fault_checker.

Fixes bug: 1216961
Change-Id: I8be959fc2ef941f89347245a3077eba623824760

commit_message:
Stop stack updates from exceeding resource limit

Previous patches raise an error when a newly created stack would exceed
the limit. This one applies the same logic during an update. Note that
nested stack updates will be handled in another patch.

Change-Id: Ic5d32501f582640cb77629b902c32c8cb9c20b42
Partial-Bug: #1215100

Sorry to be nitpicky on this.  The code change is good, and from the linked commit in your message I can see that the parameter was dropped.  But your test doesn't actually test that it's added back.  It's a good test, but doesn't cover the change you're making to the code.

Can you add a test that ensures the parameter is passed properly?"}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2013-09-10 14:21:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Andrew - the test actually check that the parameter is passed correctly. I'll try and explain. When the driver starts the value self._datastore_regex is set (i.e. self.conn._datastore_regex). In the case of the test it will be '.*', which has been set in setUp. When the object for the cluster is created this is set on the object (via a parameter in VMwareVMOps) - this will be self.conn._resources[node]['vmops']._datastore_regex for the specific cluster. 
So the test check that the configuration variable is actually set on the object tht is used. This is done by:
self.assertEqual(self.conn._datastore_regex,
self.conn._resources[node]['vmops']._datastore_regex)

commit_message:
VMware: datastore regex not honoured

Commit 9408d79e7413aadcba52a61b7a33164090785e4f did not pass the
datastore regular expression to the VMOps class. This resulted in the
configured parameter being ignored.

Fixes bug: 1222349

Change-Id: I0c7619b281662121f353c04e07331404d747b28b

commit_message:
Remove default root_helper of sudo for remotefs

This patch removes the default root_helper of sudo
for the RemoteFsClient.  We should be using the
cinder.utils.get_root_helper()

Fixes Bug #1223879

Change-Id: I8ba61cd6ac09b85b9ca924a9cf43c2dcea8e6c15

Configuration reference docs for Cinder backup.

Documentation for configuration cinder-backup service
including documentation for the drivers in Havana:
Ceph, IBM TSM and Swift.
Driver documentation is based on the driver's code and comments.

Closes-Bug: 1205359

commit_message:
Fix validate.py and test.py traversals

The get_modified_files call needs to be run from the doc directory
since we invoce it with --relative.

I noticed that we skipped validation of files in some case
and confirmed that this is now handled properly.

Change-Id: Ieaa5bfb2f7ada6345dba8b6b4116f17dff582fe1
Closes-Bug: #1228777

Database
Some of the unit tests make queries against an sqlite database [3]. By default, the test database (tests.sqlite) is deleted and recreated each time run_tests.sh is invoked (This is equivalent to using the -r, --recreate-db flag). To reduce testing time if a database already exists it can be reused by using the flag:

-n, --no-recreate-db

commit_message:
Add an option of no-recreating db when developers run unit test

-n, --no-recreate-db
If a db already exists it can be reused by using the flag
Don't receate db to reduce testing time

Fixes bug 1219040

Change-Id: If7658739b8b1c397a43371c44f2b02d878222664

commit_message:
assert_ is deprecated, use assertEqual

All of the assert_ (which is actually assertTrue) were just
comparisons, so I switched to assertEqual instead.

Change-Id: Ie2fe5ccd5d546cc4a3eccdc008b066ffe905b294

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-20 02:33:50.000000000', 'message': 'Fix Instance secgroup update error with Nova secgroup

Nova add/remove_security_group takes secgroup name instead of id.
Add api test for update_instance_security_group in api.nova.

Change the parameter name "new_sgs" of server_update_security_groups
to "new_security_group_ids" to clarify it takes ID as a parameter.

Based on the initial patch in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/39940

commit_message:
Fix Instance secgroup update error with Nova secgroup

Nova add/remove_security_group takes secgroup name instead of id.
Add api test for update_instance_security_group in api.nova.

Change the parameter name "new_sgs" of server_update_security_groups
to "new_security_group_ids" to clarify it takes ID as a parameter.

Based on the initial patch in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/39940

Change-Id: I8d9b6f5c22eee5adbaea51ce352483ab74f488f6
Closes-Bug: #1207184

commit_message:
Require python-novaclient>=2.15.0

Havana Cinder requires new novaclient functionality for
qemu-assisted-snapshots (create/delete_volume_snapshot) and
volume migration (update_server_volume).

commit_message:
Remove the get_service_id method and inline python

Keystone client's endpoint-list now returns the service id associated
with each endpoint.

Fixes Bug# 1223534

Change-Id: I2ff56803f5f9d1f57a8fc1eabaf5ac5b13310b6d

commit_message:
Tolerate bad environment until validation

Currently if we get a bad environment for a template_resource,
it causes an exception in the resource constructor, which does cause
the stack create to fail, but also all subsequent operations too.

By tolerating the error in the constructor, we can catch it instead at
validation time.

Change-Id: Ia971d8f1c50ca6f265ec36ea564aeba1638de541
Closes-Bug: 1227816

Test that Heat max_template_size is applied

Heat should be refusing any template larger than this value at the API
level.

Change-Id: I8a7d4929dce162f4c6ed41c1b4fd71493a177ece

commit_message:
Cleanup and consolidation of the roles to cover all-in-one installation.

There were a number of unreferenced and required recipes that needed roles.
There were also several roles that were redundant or referred to recipes that
did not exist, so they were removed.

deleted: os-block-storage-worker.rb no recipe
deleted: os-identity-api-admin.rb redundant
deleted: os-identity-api.rb unnecessarily fine-grained
deleted: os-infra-caching.rb unused

new: os-block-storage-volume.rb Cinder volume service
new: os-compute-conductor.rb Nova conductor service
new: os-compute-setup.rb Nova setup and identity registration

Change-Id: Ibdbfd8929669caa2d0771eeaad9f79f727e14867
modified: Berksfile.lock
modified: infrastructure.yml all roles captured
modified: os-block-storage.rb roll-up role now refers to the roles
modified: os-compute-api.rb added base role
modified: os-compute-single-controller.rb added openstack-ops-database::openstack-db, os-compute-setup and os-compute-conductor
modified: os-dashboard.rb removed openstack-ops-database::openstack-db, doesn't belong here
modified: os-image-api.rb removed openstack-ops-database::openstack-db, doesn't belong here
modified: os-image-registry.rb removed openstack-ops-database::openstack-db, doesn't belong here
modified: os-network.rb refer to network::common per Johannes Becker's catch
modified: os-object-storage.rb refer to the os-object-storage roles

commit_message:
Details on NVP implementation of Provider network extension

Provide more information on how flat and vlan networks are supported in
the backend, and discuss how the max_lp_per_bridged_ls should be tuned
according to the NVP version running in the backend

Bug 1227592

Change-Id: I339c4f0eb9f78d586d249d754084962387db8579

Fix logbook resumption.

Currently resuming via a logbook is not working after
the persistence adjustments. This change fixes that and
makes it work again.

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-08-31 14:35:49.000000000', 'message': "remove multi_host check for dhcp checksum

This removes the conditional check that actives the workaround
for adding dhcp checksums so that dhcp will work with older clients.
This check is necessary for single host configurations as well as
multi host once as some single code configurations (such as devstack)
will have multiple VM's on one machine with a local dhcp server.

This workaround will save a lot of headache with devstack since without

commit_message:
remove multi_host check for dhcp checksum

This removes the conditional check that actives the workaround
for adding dhcp checksums so that dhcp will work with older clients.
This check is necessary for single host configurations as well as
multi host once as some single code configurations (such as devstack)
will have multiple VM's on one machine with a local dhcp server.

This workaround will save a lot of headache with devstack since without
devstack may mysteriously refuse to work because of dhcp problems.

Change-Id: I53e7e285c5b44dfb6880040b5cd5dba24d13a4cc

commit_message:
Consider lc string for bootable True/False

The xml.volumes_client check to translate the bootable
setting on a volume object only checks for Upper case strings
and bools.

It turns out that this test was introduced after a bug was introduced
to cinder.api which inadvertently changed the type used to set this
member field.  We now have a patch to fix this and put it back to "true/false"
(lc strings) but since the change there's a tempest test that verifies this.

This patch will check for string true/false either lc or uc, and will
keep the bool check in place as well (otherwise everything will fail).

This test did such a great job we should consider removing the other options
for true/false representations which would've caught the original error introduced
in Cinder (reference cinder lp# 1227837.

Fixes bug: 1227858

Change-Id: I8a4b1f4ce3a6a420e8152ea8c66a9b3fc127fe96

commit_message:
Replace OpenStack LLC with OpenStack Foundation

Some files still use trademark OpenStack LLC in header, which
should be changed to OpenStack Foundation.

NOTE: tools/install_venv.py is not synced from oslo-incubator, so
it is modified too.

Change-Id: I0084684ff5225076291fea857eb010d638291bd0
Fixes-Bug: #1214176

commit_message:
Update default db username to keystone

The current default db username for keystone is
keystone_admin. This is inconsistent with the default
db username for every other service which use the
same name as the name of the service.

The documented installation instruction for keystone
also use keystone as the database user.

This commit updates the default to use keystone instead of
keyston_admin.

Change-Id: I1cfaf3fbbc691ff9dbef415b69492f9f965dc113

commit_message:
reschedule_or_error will detach other instances' volumes on Cinder side

When a user creates (in error) an instance using volumes
 which is already in use by another instance,
the error is correctly detected.
But the _reschedule_or_error function will incorrectly
 detach all BDM-volumes given in request, regardless off
 whether each volume had been attached to instance or not.

So we need a protection here,
volume-rollback would only permit to detach the volume
 which is truly belonging to the instance.

Fixes bug: 1215012
Change-Id: Ic0b3527bb68ccf151f31252c931e79193cc6f579

commit_message:
Change usage of assertTrue / assertFalse

The usage of assertTrue() is to be changed to assertIn,
assertIsNone, assertEquals where ever return is not explicit boolean

Change-Id: Ia9b6a6e4fe213392da7db7f5ead37963bf5c9656
Fixes: bug #1218713

I had apparently *imagined* that DLO had purposely *reserved* the leading slash with aspirations of a "unified-cross-account" syntax for COPY/DLO and other features with similar semantics where the leading slash would mean the "path" is in the format of "/account/container/prefix" instead of "container/prefix/moreprefix" It'd be nice if we were consistent here. If we could turn back the clock to 1.8 - I'd say we should add the restriction to SLO. Since the format of COPY/X-Copy-From is not persistent beyond the request, it's semantics could always be changed if someday we ever do a Swift API v2.0 - but SLO's are to disk so will X-Object-Manifest be after this change. At this point I'm not sure if there's a clean way to make up a syntax for path that allows you specify a different account and still allow COPY to maintain it's leniency on unquoting. I suppose we may as well be consistent in the mean time. I probably dreamed up this reserved unified-cross-account syntax anyway.'}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2013-09-10 21:36:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this If you PUT an object with an empty X-Object-Manifest, this code crashes. commit_message:
Removes leading slash on X-Object-Manifest value

The swift api currently returns a 400 value when submitting a
X-Object-Manifest beginning with a /.

This strips the leading slash from the X-Object-Manifest value.

This also removes the test case that checks for a bad http request
returned.

Users can now submit X-Object-Manifest values with a leading slash.

Fixes: bug #1191958
Change-Id: I2711c2fa634ba8b47681562b4674235b54ac457a

commit_message:
Fix pending_delete images with NULL location

Scrubber needs the location metadata to do cleanup.
However RegistryClient.get_images_detailed() returns
pending_delete images with NULL location.

Fix this by allowing location to be returned for
pending_delete images in db api.

Change-Id: Ib2b666c2f0b5cd9b89120b0650a03777415bbe16
Fixes: bug #1190643

commit_message:
Add Guru Meditation Report Functionality to Apps

Adds Guru Meditation Report hooks to all of the nova components.
Now, all components may be sent SIGUSR1 to print the basic
Guru Meditation Report to stderr

Change-Id: I42601201a25a4d6c4065489d8db9441d0554a1c7
Implements: bp-guru-meditation-report

Enable swift integration

Added code to facilitate the installation of the swift integration jar
and allow for the setting of required swift properties (both general
and provider specific)

Fixes: bug #1227303

commit_message:
Get ambari mirror with curl instead of wget

That was implemented in 0.2 but wasn't 'backported' back to 0.3.
The rationale is that unlike 'curl', 'wget' is not installed by
default on CentOS

Change-Id: I16c920dcb0b496fd229754c49ba7ed9fe19ad1e8

commit_message:
Update documentation for sql_connection credentials

Lets use the same username and password the database server setups by
default.  Otherwise, following the examples will result in a password /
user mismatch.

Change-Id: Ieee67b5912bb823a3b422752bb7f7e30bbba4897
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <paul.belanger@polybeacon.com>

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-09-15 16:28:05.000000000', 'message': 'Increase swift storage

Swift storage is used as glance image back-end. Tempest have cinder to
uploads 1 GiB image from cinder in twice.

In parallel execution in cause an issue, bacuse the current size is
2_000_000 KiB.

Increasing the swit storage size from 2_000_000 KiB 4_000_000 KiB for
gate jobs.

Fixing bug 1225664

Change-Id: I421d8ee6fc6cbde463592134832d169f91d8a91b
'}, {'created': '2013-09-18 14:37:07.000000000', 'message': 'Let devstack to decide about swift storage

Besed on several discussion, the right swift storage size value should
be configured by devstack and not by devstack gate.

Fixing bug 1225664

Change-Id: I421d8ee6fc6cbde463592134832d169f91d8a91b
'}]
commit_message:
Let devstack to decide about swift storage

Besed on several discussion, the right swift storage size value should
be configured by devstack and not by devstack gate.

Fixing bug 1225664

Change-Id: I421d8ee6fc6cbde463592134832d169f91d8a91b

commit_message:
Update cinder flags with autogenerate tools

Also create new tables cinder-backups_ceph, cinder-backup_swift,
cinder_backups_tsm, cinder-gpfs_volume so that the tables can
be used by these patches:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/47118
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/47044/

Additional tables have been split up so that they can be used
in the configuration reference.

Change-Id: Ic87f80d4604bd9fdb5d8f9d3b0e0fe69dffb1e40

commit_message:
Add ordereddict for python 2.6 compatibility

Glance property protections (bp/api-v2-property-protection) is
predicated on sections in a configuration file being read in the order
they appear.

This is the default behaviour for ConfigParser in Python 2.7, however
for Python 2.6 we need to specify the 'dict_type' parameter
(ref
http://docs.python.org/2/library/configparser.html#ConfigParser.RawConfigParser
)

This dependency can be removed when OpenStack is no longer required to
support Python 2.6.

Change-Id: Iafe9d1ffe2062156c5194b491c7fe55b130a7461

commit_message:
Update tox to use develop and custom pip command

The use_develop option saves time over the sdist/install. More
importantly, install_command allows us to override tox's default
behavior of passing --pre.

Change-Id: Ifb8fc877aa23db38310777912aa6d914ae040178

commit_message:
Catch more accuracy exception for _lookup_by_name

When an instance is not found by libvirtd, _lookup_by_name in libvirt
driver raises InstanceNotFound. This patch catchs this exception instead
of NotFound who is the father of InstanceNotFound.

Closes-Bug: #1222663
Change-Id: I1b4ce8f6c44eef29617a42151152cda2159a0088

[{'created': '2013-09-20 15:45:59.000000000', 'message': 'Fix HP3PAR iSCSI path connection

The iSCSI paths are not correctly identified as ‘active’
when port information is requested from the hp3parclient
because the ‘active’ value is a Boolean not the string
‘true’.

Fixes Bug #1224594

Change-Id: Ib10563cfc31c0628dc8b1edbba246398a3a11f34
'}]
commit_message:
Fix HP3PAR iSCSI path connection

The iSCSI paths are not correctly identified as ‘active’
when port information is requested from the hp3parclient
because the ‘active’ value is a Boolean not the string
‘true’.

Fixes Bug #1224594

Change-Id: Ib10563cfc31c0628dc8b1edbba246398a3a11f34

commit_message:
Fix problem with starting Windows 7 instances using VMware Driver

The default controller for a Windows 7 virtual machine is the
LSI Logic SAS. When the disk adapter type is specified as 'lsiLogic'
via glance image metadata, VMware driver defaults to LSI Logic Parallel
controller. With this fix the driver will honor a property 'lsiLogicsas'
to distinguish the right adapter and enable booting Windows instances.

Fixes: bug #1187853
Change-Id: Idb36a784a31e4938e8951adeb83335b3890dac85

commit_message:
Implement unix domain socket consoles for libvirt

For this change to work for you, you'll need to either disable
apparmor or alter the libvirt templates to allow access to
/tmp. You also need to change the value of the
console_log_type flag to "domain". Console logs are then passed
from libvirt to nova-compute with a unix domain socket. This
allows us to implement console log file rotation.

This change also makes the way file system elements are shared
with libvirt configurable. You can specify a chmod value for
those elements (the previous implementation), or a group to
chgrp to which is shared by nova-compute and libvirt. If
neither option is specified, nova-compute will refuse to start
if using the libvirt hypervisor driver.

This change also slightly refactors how all console logging in
libvirt works, but there are no functional changes to "file"
style logging.

New flags:
    console_log_type
    max_rotated_consoles

    libvirt_shared_file_mode
    libvirt_shared_group
    libvirt_shared_noop

DocImpact

SecurityImpact: this should reduce the amount of unbounded
growth we see in libvirt console log files.

Closes-Bug: 832507
Closes-Bug: 1227027
Progresses blueprint fix-libvirt-console-logging

commit_message:
xenapi: Make rescue safer

If rescue setup fails, detach the root disk from the rescue VM so it
doesn't get nuked by the undo stack logic in spawn()

bug 1227898

Change-Id: I8864b4c524f04f7b387be1018fea9919a461c48b

[{'created': '2013-07-30 03:20:28.000000000', 'message': 'Add retry to remove old inst_base when resize-revert vm

Fix bug 1206312

When resize revert one VM instance, if the NFS is slow, the NFS
mounted on source host might not respond quickly. This will cause
that even if the VM instance configuration files was deleted from
resize target host, the NFS on source host may still think the
files were not deleted. Then in driver.py::finish_revert_migration,
the driver try to delete the file again, this will lead nova compute
throw exception.

The fix was add retry logic, if failed to delete the instance, retry
again till it is removed.

Change-Id: I89990c1750a7fd7f421cab03780e7704ee661de1

commit_message:
libvirt: ignore false exception due to slow NFS on resize-revert

When resize revert one VM instance, if the NFS is slow, the NFS
mounted on source host might not respond quickly. This will cause
that even if the VM instance configuration files was deleted from
resize target host, the NFS on source host may still think the
files were not deleted. Then in driver.py::finish_revert_migration,
the driver try to delete the file again, this will lead nova compute
throw exception.

The fix was ignore exception for such case: if failed to delete the
instance with error no as 2 (No such file or directory)

Fix bug 1206312

Change-Id: I89990c1750a7fd7f421cab03780e7704ee661de1

commit_message:
Actually fix info_cache healing lazy load

system_metadata is still being lazy loaded as a part of healing the
instance info_cache.  A previous attempt to fix this issue missed the
more important call.

It's actually more efficient to not load the system_metadata when getting
the list and allow the 1 instance to lazy load.  For the cached instances,
we will ask for system_metadata when getting a fresh copy from the DB.

Fixes bug 1223969

Change-Id: Ib95e868135ed2b36af7ddbcfb8d5905bfe14d1fe

commit_message:
Configurable libvirt sharing options

Previously we have assumed that we just chmod everything which
needs to be shared with libvirt to 777. This change makes that
configurable.

DocImpact: adds two flags (libvirt_shared_file_mode and
libvirt_shared_group) which let you specify what is needed for
nova-compute to share filesystem elements with libvirt.

Progresses blueprint fix-libvirt-console-logging.

Change-Id: I5d1cb79375a2ed509262f19af93fa2946e1edf3c

commit_message:
Implement file rotate for unix domain console logging

This change adds console log file rotation to the unix domain
socket logging implementation. It also slightly refactors the
way file logging is handled, but there are no functional changes.

Resolves bug 832507, progresses blueprint fix-libvirt-console-logging.

DocImpact: console log files are now rotated if unix domain
socket logging is turned on.

SecurityImpact: this should reduce the amount of unbounded
growth we see in libvirt console log files.

Change-Id: I0fd2f225c7637eb95d82e5dc465313cb7b5c0620

subject: Add support for unix domain sockets as console logs
